==English==

===Etymology===
{{Gr.}} ''[[Ουρανός]]''<!--Ουρανός--> (ouranos), heaven, sky

===Pronunciation===
*[[RP]]: /ˈjʊrənəs/ ''or'' /jʊˈreɪnəs/
*[[WEAE]]: /ˈjurənəs/ ''or'' /juˈreɪnəs/

===Proper noun===
'''Uranus''' ''m'', genitive '''Urani'''

Second declension

#<!--GreekDeitySkyHeaven-->(''Greek mythology'') The god of the sky and heavens, son and husband to [[Gaia]], with whom he fathered the [[Titan]]s.
#<!--Planet7-->''(Astronomy):'' The seventh [[planet]] from the sun, in our [[solar system]].

